A freelance journalist who worked for Reuters was among more than 50 people killed when gunmen attacked a local government building in the Iraqi town of Tikrit.Sabah al-Bazee, 30, who had contributed to the agency since 2004 and also worked as cameraman for several other media organisations, died from shrapnel wounds in an explosion."On behalf of the entire team at Thomson Reuters, I wish to convey our sadness at the untimely death of Sabah al-Bazee," said Reuters editor-in-chief Stephen Adler."He was a valued member of our team in Iraq and will be much missed by colleagues. This tragic incident shows yet again the risks journalists face daily in doing their jobs and to bring news to the world."Several Reuters colleagues have paid tribute to Sabah in a blog posting.Source: Reuters